# Hearst Design System - Tailwind CSS Approach

## CRITICAL: Use Tailwind Classes with CSS Variables

When creating or modifying any component, use **Tailwind CSS classes** that reference our design tokens defined in `globals.css`. This enables automatic theme switching via the `data-theme` attribute.

## Preferred Approach: Tailwind Classes

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use Tailwind classes
<div className="bg-neutral-200 p-5 rounded-lg border border-neutral-400">
  <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-1000">Title</h1>
  <p className="text-base text-neutral-700">Content</p>
</div>

// ❌ AVOID - Inline styles with designTokens (legacy)
<div style={{ backgroundColor: colors.neutral[200], padding: spacing.lg }}>
```

